post.body: Following some new real estate tweeps cuz they always know what's going on.
Remember job security? Me neither.
Let's be honest. New Years Eve blows. Yeah, I said it. What?
Oh wait, I forgot that Twitter isn't supposed to be about what I ate for lunch. Sorry, but those planks were twelicious
I'm thinking that my Long John Silvers meal was worth every second taken from my life expectancy
The answer to Austin's traffic problem: All of you who went away for the holidays, stay where you are.
This year I'm going to hunt less and farm more
Reading The World Without Us by Alan Weisman. Enlightening.
Where can I pick up some yummy tamales in Austin?
Last minute shopping at Lakeline Mall was surprisingly pleasant. Maybe procrastination is the way to go
